The binary files are native executables for the ANTLR tool itself (not
 the run-time support etc...).
You do not have to have Java on your system now to use ANTLR for
C++, C#, or Python output.  Even for Java users, it is still more convenient
to run this binary as it loads faster and you don't have CLASSPATH issues.
<br>
<br>
Luca Di Gaspero provided a <a href="/share/1069557132934/makefile.gcj"><b>makefile</b></a> so you can use GCJ to build your own.<br>
